“Avengers: Endgame’ runtime is still at 3 hours, says Joe Russo

Los Angeles:

The runtime of “Avengers: Endgame”, sitting at close to three hours, is set to top the length of its predecessor “Avengers: Infinity War”.

In an interview with Collider, Joe Russo, one half of director duo The Russo Brothers, said the runtime will be at three hours and Disney has no problems with it.

“I think the studio is down with what the best story is. Right now, we think the…

body:
You Didn’t See That Coming

Chapter 4

Summary: Unfortunately in the compound, arguments happen a lot, especially when a new team member arrives.

Words: 711

Notes/Warnings: arguing, maybe a bit angsty idk, I accidentally posted chapter 5 instead of this one. Please leave feedback if you like the fic so far!

Master List

—

“Rhodey, you’re burning the french toast.”

He flipped the pieces he was watching, which were starting to turn almost black at the edges. “Oh well, I’ll have those ones.”

“Why do we trust Rhodey to make the french toast?” Sam asked, coming over to grab another slice.

“Cause no one else volunteers to help me,” Anna responded, “they’d rather just sit and play video games.” She shot a pointed look over at Nat and Tony, who were sitting on the couch playing Overwatch. Both of them ignored her.

“I can help if you’d like,” Steve offered.

“It’s fine, I can make the last of it. There’s almost enough for everyone.” Anna replied.

“Speaking of everyone,” Nat added, “where’s Pietro?”

“Knowing him, he’s probably still asleep,” Wanda replied.

“Yeah, he was when I woke up at least,” Anna added.

“Peter’s not up yet either,” Tony added.

As if on cue, Peter walked in.

“I am now,” he said, coming over to grab a plate of french toast.

I wonder what he’ll think of our newest arrival, Anna thought.

“Has anyone told him yet?” She asked.

“Told me what?” Peter responded.

“Pietro’s back,” Wanda told him.

“Wait, he’s back? How?” He questioned.

“He wasn’t actually dead, he’s been in a coma and just recently woke up,” Anna explained.

“Ah, ok,” Peter replied, heading over to sit with Tony and Rhodey.

After a few moments of peace and quiet, interrupted by the occasional complaints at the video game, Pietro came in. Unfortunately he was running at super speed and misjudged the distances, causing him to slide straight into the wall.

Anna and Wanda both burst out laughing.

Natasha gave a small chuckle as well, “you alright Pietro?”

“I’m fine,” he replied, “with the speed I keep messing up distances, I’m used to running into things by now.”

“There’s french toast for breakfast if you’d like some,” Tony said.

Anna could barely even see him moving, one second he hadn’t moved, the next he was sitting off to the side of the living room with some french toast.

“Are you ever going to slow down, Pietro?” Wanda asked him, exasperated.

“No, I’m not,” he replied.

Quiet again. Then, “Hey Tony, do you know when we’ll be getting an actual room set up for Pietro?”

“It’ll probably be awhile, sorry,” Tony replied, “you surviving sharing?”

“Yeah, so far,” Anna replied, “well, except for the fact that we aren’t getting along very well, but it’ll be alright.”

“You aren’t getting along?”

“Not really. I’m trying, but he seemed determined to not like me,” Anna mumbled.

“Anna,” Tony said softly, “has it occurred to you why he’s like this?”

“No,” she started, “I can’t see why-”

Oh, it’s because I’m a Stark.

Well, this is going to be interesting…

“Just give him time,” Tony said, “I’m sure he’ll get over it eventually.”

“I seriously doubt that,” Pietro added. Tony glared at him.

Sensing that an argument could get out of hand, Wanda stepped in. “Pietro, you probably will get over it after awhile. I did.”

“You did?”

“Of course I did, Anna’s my best friend, I could never hate her,” Wanda said, “I know it’ll probably be difficult for you to get over this. But trust me it will be worth it.”

“And blaming us for what happened isn’t going to get you anywhere. I didn’t have any involvement in the weapons program, and Tony did it to try and help people, when he realised that the weapons weren’t being used for good he shut it down immediately. You’re judging us for things that happened years ago, we can’t change the past.”

“Yes,” Pietro responded, “but neither of you understand. You don’t have any idea what it was like, and you can’t just expect me to ‘get over it’ that simply.”

“Actually, we do understand,” Tony snapped back, “and I don’t expect instant forgiveness. All I want is for you to keep Anna out of this, don’t blame her for my mistakes.”

“Ok, can we just end this conversation please?” Anna asked, “before this gets worse.”

Everyone quietens, finishing their food in silence. They go their separate ways for the day, but Anna can’t help the feeling of dread creeping through her. This isn’t the end of this.

body:
Avocado

*Valentine’s Day*

Peter: Hey, MJ, do you like avocados?

MJ: No…

Peter: Because I wouldn’t mind avo-cuddling with you…?

Peter: *realises MJ said ‘no’*

Peter: WAIT SORRY I DIDN’T—

MJ: *smiles* I wouldn’t mind avo-cuddling with you, either.

Peter: *blushes*

title: Monster
body:
“Have you ever asked yourself, do monsters make war, or does war make monsters?”

Six

I paced back and forth in my living room as I waited for Rogers to arrive. I’d spent most of the afternoon furiously scrubbing the place clean just to keep my mind from wandering. I hadn’t seen…
